.SH NAME
Time::Zone \- miscellaneous timezone manipulations routines
.SH VERSION
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 2.35
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 9
\&    use Time::Zone;
\&    print tz2zone();
\&    print tz2zone($ENV{\*(AqTZ\*(Aq});
\&    print tz2zone($ENV{\*(AqTZ\*(Aq}, time());
\&    my $isdst = 0;
\&    print tz2zone($ENV{\*(AqTZ\*(Aq}, undef, $isdst);
\&    my $offset = tz_local_offset();
\&    my $TZ = "EST";
\&    $offset = tz_offset($TZ);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a collection of miscellaneous timezone manipulation routines.
.PP
\&\f(CWtz2zone()\fR parses the TZ environment variable and returns a timezone
string suitable for inclusion in \fBdate\fR\|(1)\-like output.  It optionally takes
a timezone string, a time, and a is\-dst flag.
.PP
\&\f(CWtz_local_offset()\fR determines the offset from GMT time in seconds.  It
only does the calculation once.
.PP
\&\f(CWtz_offset()\fR determines the offset from GMT in seconds of a specified
timezone.
.PP
\&\f(CWtz_name()\fR determines the name of the timezone based on its offset
.SH NAME
Time::Zone \-\- miscellaneous timezone manipulations routines
